{
  "doc_id": "44849",
  "text": "A directed path in digraph G is a sequence of directed edges. A directed tree is a digraph in which, for the root i and any other node j, there exists exactly one directed path from i to j. A spanning tree of a digraph is a directed tree formed by graph edges that connect all the nodes of the graph [CITATION_1] . Graph G is called strongly connected if and only if any two distinct nodes can be connected via a directed path and quasi-strongly connected if and only if it has a directed spanning tree [CITATION_2] .",
